The Corporeal Beast is the physical incarnation of the Spirit Beast, and is a boss monster. It requires completion of Summer's End to fight. The Corporeal Beast was brought into existence when the Spirit Beast was killed at the end of Summer's End; as everything within the Spirit Realm represents the opposite of its version on Gielinor, the death of the Spirit Beast in the Spirit Realm caused the creation of the Corporeal Beast in Gielinor. The Corporeal Beast resides in the Gielinor version of the caverns in which the Spirit Beast was trapped and destroyed.

The Corporeal Beast possesses a number of formidable abilities that distinguish it from similarly-levelled boss monsters. It has very high accuracy and damage. It is also capable of eating summoning familiars and legendary pets who are serving as Beast of Burden. Though it has no weaknesses, its thick armour greatly reduces the damage of all non-spear weapons. It can also summon dark energy cores to attack players and siphon their health as its own. If the Corporeal Beast eats your Beast of Burden and you attempt to summon a different familiar that is not a Beast of Burden, the items from the previously devoured familiar will be dropped on the ground.

The Corporeal Beast is the only monster to drop the arcane, divine, elysian, and spectral sigils, used to create the spirit shields. In addition to its sigil drops, the Corporeal Beast has many other valuable drops.

Obtaining all unique drops will unlock the Dark Core [Name] title.

Getting there[edit | edit source]

The location of the cavern

The Corporeal Beast can be found at the end of a series of three large chambers. The entrance to the caverns is located in level 33 Wilderness, not far from the Graveyard of Shadows. The cavern can only be entered if the Gielinor version of the cave is not collapsed; otherwise, players must head into the Spirit Realm and collapse that version before the Gielinor version is open again.

However, players who have completed Summer's End may use a games necklace to teleport directly into the first of the caverns, or use the PvM portal to bring them right outside the chamber it resides in. Attempting to leave the caverns back out into the Wilderness while opted into PvP will cause a Wilderness warning prompt to appear before the player can continue.

Though the caves' entrance is in the Wilderness, the caverns themselves and the Corporeal Beast's lair are not dangerous Wilderness territory, as PVP and Wilderness level are disabled here. Before entering its room, players may investigate the passage and select the "Peek in" option to see a zoomed-in view of the Corporeal Beast's spawn point, in order to determine whether or not any other players are currently fighting it in uninstanced encounter.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 17 January 2022 (Update):
    • The player will now be sent back to the game world as expected whenever leaving the Corporeal Beast's cave.
  • hotfix 25 May 2021:
    • Update of 24 May 2021 introduced a bug, where it was no longer possible to set-up and place Dwarven and Invention multicannons in several allowed instanced areas, such as the Corporeal Beast boss instance. This has been hotfixed.
  • patch 11 January 2021 (Update):
    • Various bosses around RuneScape have taken their Santa Hats off for another year.
  • patch 4 May 2020 (Update):
    • Adamantite stone spirits replaced with necrite and phasmatite stone spirits.
  • patch 27 January 2020 (Update):
    • A kill timer is now available at Kalphite Queen and the Corporeal Beast.
  • patch 3 May 2016 (Update):
    • Ironmen can no longer enter the Corporeal Beast's non-instanced encounter the first time they attempt enter the cavern.
  • ninja 25 April 2016 (Update):
    • Improved respawn rates for Corporeal Beast.
  • patch 16 March 2015 (Update):
    • It is now possible to use surge in the Corporeal Beast boss instances.
  • patch 9 August 2011 (Update):
    • Dark cores now render on top of the player.
  • patch 28 March 2011 (Update):
    • A tile in the Corporeal Beast's lair no longer causes players to go invisible.
  • patch 1 February 2011 (Update):
    • It is no longer possible to spawn too many energy cores while fighting the Corporeal Beast.
  • patch 6 October 2010 (Update):
    • Adjusted the Corporeal Beast's Adventurer's Log entry.
  • patch 7 October 2009 (Update):
    • Fixed the colours of the Corporeal Beast's animations in Standard Detail.
  • patch 27 January 2009 (Update):
    • The warning when entering the Corporeal Beast's cave can now be turned off.
  • patch 15 October 2008 (Update):
    • The Corporeal beast now has a stomp attack that hurts players standing underneath him.
  • update 15 September 2008 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • During the 9 June 2009 game engine update glitch, players could solo the Corporeal Beast because it would not retaliate using Magic. It could, however, use its stomp attack.
  • An update to the Ring of Wealth on 15 March 2011 caused the sigil drop table to be landed on 100% of the time with LootShare enabled. This bug was patched within an hour of its release. Jagex later issued a statement with an apology and revealed that there would be no rollbacks.
  • After killing the Corporeal Beast, a player's Adventurer's Log will say "I killed the Corporeal Beast, a vision of supernatural horror." Killing more than one will result in "I killed X Corporeal Beasts, all visions of supernatural horror."
  • Like Revenants, it is possible for the Corporeal Beast to ignore the player and move around even if under attack.
  • Before the Evolution of Combat, Divine and Elysian had a 1 in 8 chance each when hitting the sigil drop table and Spectral and Arcane had a 3 in 8 chance each.[3]>
  • The Corporeal Beast used to have a special attack called Stomp. It activated when players stood under it. This attack could hit over 4,500 damage. The Corporeal Beast did not have this attack when it was released; the Stomp attack was added one month later on 15 October 2008 in order to prevent players from hiding underneath it, and replaced with new mechanics on 12 September 2016.
    • Despite this, the "Learn" section for the boss still states that it possesses a stomp attack.
  • As of 1 February 2018, the highest kill count for this boss was 36,426 kills.[4]
    • This had increased to 62,725 by 13 December 2018.[5]
  • The Corporeal Beast used to drop 100 teak planks at a time. It was changed to 150 in a hidden update sometime between May 2021 and May 2023.
